<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCD6A72FCF39F1816F5BA9D" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCD6A72FCF39F1816F5BA9D" blockId="54.[782,1378,2250,2679]" lastBlockId="54.[1446,2660,280,2525]" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">
This species, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC2B9F181AA4B250" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[983,1188,2369,2402]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">Hypsugo petersi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB049F181D40B2BB" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">H. mordax</taxonomicName>
were previously placed in Pipustrellus, where the first two were treated in the “ 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FCE19FEE1D6FB2EA" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[797,879,2487,2520]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
group” (with some other Asian species) by G. H. H. Tate in 1942, and by K. F. Koopman in 1994. In 1987, based mainly on bacular characters of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FAEC9C741B61B17C" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1296,1377,2605,2638]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FCB09C031D9BB145" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[844,923,2650,2679]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">petersi</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC529C031A10B145" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[942,1040,2650,2679]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
was not included in the study), J. E. Hill and D. L. Harrison redefined the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC739C251DE0B1AF" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[911,992,2684,2717]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
group, limiting it to these three species (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FE809CFA1FDFB1F6" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[380,479,2723,2756]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
tentatively), which they placed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB589CFA1B37B1F6" authorityName="Troughton" authorityYear="1943" box="[1188,1335,2723,2756]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Falsistrellus</taxonomicName>
of Pipustrellus, alongside the Australian forms 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FD039C931DA1B1D9" authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1858" box="[767,929,2762,2795]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tasmaniensis">tasmaniensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC169C931A70B1D9" authorityName="Kitchener, Caputi &amp; B. Jones" authorityYear="1986" box="[1002,1136,2762,2795]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mackenziei">mackenziei</taxonomicName>
(the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB429C931B60B1D9" authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1858" box="[1214,1376,2762,2795]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tasmaniensis">tasmaniensis</taxonomicName>
group). G. B. Corbet and Hill followed this arrangement in 1992, whereas in 2005 N. B. Simmons recognized 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FDD59D401CBDB008" authorityName="Troughton" authorityYear="1943" box="[553,701,2841,2874]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Falsistrellus</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus, with the same five species. The phylogenetic studies of L.. R. Heaney and colleagues in 2012 and M. Ruedi and colleagues in 2017, revealed a close relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FCA69D301DAAB0B8" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[858,938,2921,2954]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">petersi</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC259D301A48B0B8" box="[985,1096,2921,2954]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
. On the basis of sequence data of mitochondrial and nuclear genes, and combining cranial, dental, and multivariate statistical evidence, in 2018 T. Gorfol and G. Csorba (and in 2019 Gorfol and colleagues) recovered 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FDDE9D861C72B732" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[546,626,3039,3072]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">petersi</taxonomicName>
within a clade of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC9B9D861DD6B732" box="[871,982,3039,3072]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
, with a sister relationship to H. dolichodon; as a result they transferred the Asian members of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FBE79A561AB0B71A" authorityName="Troughton" authorityYear="1943" box="[1051,1200,3087,3112]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Falsistrellus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB3E9A561B17B71A" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1218,1303,3087,3112]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FAD59A561ED8B77C" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FF149A741F37B77C" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[232,311,3117,3150]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">petersi</taxonomicName>
) to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FE8E9A741FE1B77C" box="[370,481,3117,3150]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
. At the specific level, following Gorfol and Csorba, comparison between specimens of “ 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FE0B9A0C1C47B744" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[503,583,3157,3190]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
” from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FD539A0C1D34B744" box="[687,820,3157,3190]" name="Myanmar" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(Mon State) and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FBCA9A0C1AC7B744" box="[1078,1223,3157,3190]" name="Cambodia" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
and those from the Indian subcontinent revealed morphological differences (skull and dental characters, number of caudal vertebrae, bacular form), with the result that the 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FAF49AF51EE0B7DF" name="Myanmar" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FEDB9A951FB7B7DF" box="[295,439,3276,3309]" name="Cambodia" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
specimens were reidentified as H. dolichodon. Earlier, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FF569AAA1EFBB626" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[170,251,3315,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FEB29AAA1F97B626" box="[334,407,3315,3348]" name="India" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FE279AAA1C5FB626" box="[475,607,3315,3348]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
had been treated as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FBC79AAA1A99B626" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[1083,1177,3315,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
. Further studies with genetic data are needed to determine the exact distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB599B421AF5B60E" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1189,1269,3355,3388]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
and its real relationship to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FE3E9B1F1C20B651" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[450,544,3398,3427]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FD9A9B1F1CB6B651" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[614,694,3398,3427]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">petersi</taxonomicName>
, including whether they are all conspecific (the name 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FEF89B301F62B6B8" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[260,354,3433,3466]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
has priority), as was previously suspected, for example by C. M. Francis and Hill in 1986 and Corbet and Hill in 1992; comparisons ofthe three are complicated by the fact that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72F9209719193ABA53" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[1756,1850,320,353]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
is the only one with a type specimen that includes a skull. Gorfol and Csorba also reported that preliminary investigations suggested potentially undescribed forms (unpublished) in the group. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
